Durban - Two drug dealers are expected to appear in the Verulam Magistrates’ Court to face charges of dealing and possession of drugs. The dealers,aged 36 and 38, were arrested on Thursday in possession of heroine capsules. Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo, a spokesperson for the Directorate of Priority Crime Investigations (DPCI-Hawks), said members from the Durban Serious Organised Crime Investigation unit working together with Metro Police Drug Task Team and Shongweni K9 unit conducted a police operation in Verulam,north of Durban. "Members swooped on the suspects and a search was conducted in one of the suspect’s vehicle. Police found almost 2399 heroine capsules hidden in the vehicle. A further search was conducted in the suspect’s house. Police found 637 heroine capsules, 83 mandrax tablets as well as 11 broken pieces of mandrax,"Mhlongo said. The drugs, cash and the vehicle which run into thousands of rands have since been seized by police. Daily News 